SIMPLE: intermedium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermedium
<hw>In`ter*me"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Intermediums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Intermedia</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., neut. of L. <ets>intermedius</ets>
intermediate.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Intermediate space.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An intervening agent or instrument.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The bone or cartilage between the
radiale and ulnare in the carpus, and between the tibiale and fibulare
in the tarsus. It corresponds to the lunar in the carpus, and to a part
of the astragalus in the tarsus of man and most mammals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermell</ent>⟦br⟧
